# Package version bump (project-local)

> **Project-local rule.** This file is **not** from the agentic-tool catalog. Catalog
> guidance says not to hand-edit package-projected `.cursor/rules/` copies; this rule is an
> intentional **repo-specific** addition. If `agentic-tool apply` removes it, restore from
> git history (or re-add) — do not drop the requirement.

## When to bump

Any PR that merges **user-facing** or **behavior** changes to `main` **MUST** bump
`<Version>` in `src/Api2Skill/Api2Skill.csproj`.

- **Default:** patch (`X.Y.Z` → `X.Y.Z+1`).
- **Minor / major:** only when a human explicitly asks.

Agents must bump **proactively** whenever the change qualifies — **do not wait** to be told.

## When not to bump

Skip the version bump for:

- Docs-only commits (e.g. `wiki/` only, README-only, comment-only)
- Debug-folder-only commits (e.g. `debug/**` scaffolds, local OAuth fixtures)

## How to ship the bump

Include either:

1. A short commit: `chore(release): bump package version to X.Y.Z`, or
2. The bump in the **same** feature PR as the behavior change

## Tags

Do **not** create or push git tags unless a human explicitly requests it. Tagging / publishing
flow is documented in `wiki/Releasing.md`.
